          <node refid="T15" role="Co-theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>800</offset>
        <text>The trend also prevails in ecosystems subject to substantial human alteration.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>879</offset>
        <text>Across this diversity of environments, we find evidence that resource stoichiometry (organic carbon:nitrate) strongly influences nitrate accumulation by regulating a suite of microbial processes that couple dissolved organic carbon and nitrate cycling.
</text>
        <annotation id="T6">
          <infon key="type">Cause</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <infon key="brat-id">T6</infon>
          <location length="10" offset="997"/>
          <text>influences</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T16">
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <infon key="brat-id">T16</infon>
          <location length="20" offset="1008"/>
          <text>nitrate accumulation</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T17">
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <infon key="brat-id">T17</infon>
          <location length="47" offset="940"/>
          <text>resource stoichiometry (organic carbon:nitrate)</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E6">
          <infon key="type">Cause</infon>
